runtime/logs/task-point-inbox-hierarchy-propose-solutions-claude-code-yolo-anthropic-claude-opus-4-7.log:17:Recommendation in one line: keep the inbox as a **synthetic level-1 rhei with reserved id `inbox`**, materialized from an optional project-root `inbox/` directory; inbox tickets are ordinary level-2+ task nodes with project ids `inbox.<local>`, and they resolve state policy by inheriting the Panta default state machine through the same `node_policy.overrides → by_type → default` path every other rhei uses. This preserves the Panta → rhei → ticket invariant, reuses existing id rules, and avoids any new state-policy tier — at the cost of reserving `inbox` as a rhei id and accepting that the inbox cannot declare its own `**States:**` without being promoted to an authored rhei.
