runtime/logs/task-point-state-machine-resolution-aggregate-disagreements-codex-yolo-openai-gpt-5.5.log:249:+  - Options: S-002 says a non-`rhei` declared name with no matching file is a validation error and never falls back, and a `--state-machine` file whose `name` disagrees with the selected name is a validation error. S-001 needs equivalent error rules if tiers are complete selections, especially for override paths and inherited defaults.
