runtime/logs/task-point-state-machine-resolution-discuss-point-codex-yolo-openai-gpt-5.5.log:322:./runtime/logs/task-point-state-machine-resolution-propose-solutions-claude-code-yolo-anthropic-claude-opus-4-7.log:15:Proposal written to `runtime/deliberation/points/point-state-machine-resolution/proposals/claude-code-yolo-anthropic-claude-opus-4-7.md`. Core idea: split resolution into two ordered phases — **name** (rhei-local → Panta default → built-in `rhei`) then **file** (dispatched by which layer supplied the name, with `--state-machine` as a name-consistent file-level override). Errors are uniform: non-`rhei` declared name with no file = validation error; `--state-machine` name mismatch = validation error.
