runtime/logs/task-point-state-machine-resolution-discuss-point-codex-yolo-openai-gpt-5.5.log:858:./runtime/logs/task-point-state-machine-resolution-aggregate-disagreements-codex-yolo-openai-gpt-5.5.log:402:+- S-001: Single-tier precedence where the explicit invocation override is the highest-priority complete state-machine selection, followed by rhei-local `**States:**`, inherited `index.panta.md` project default, and built-in `rhei` fallback.
runtime/logs/task-point-state-machine-resolution-discuss-point-codex-yolo-openai-gpt-5.5.log:859:./runtime/logs/task-point-state-machine-resolution-aggregate-disagreements-codex-yolo-openai-gpt-5.5.log:406:+- S-002: Two-phase resolution where the effective state-machine name is selected first from rhei-local `**States:**`, inherited `index.panta.md` default, or built-in fallback; then the file is resolved based on the source of that name, with `--state-machine <path>` acting only as a file override that must match the already-selected name.
runtime/logs/task-point-state-machine-resolution-discuss-point-codex-yolo-openai-gpt-5.5.log:860:./runtime/logs/task-point-state-machine-resolution-aggregate-disagreements-codex-yolo-openai-gpt-5.5.log:408:+  - Reasons: Separates name resolution from file location to avoid layers competing to both name and locate the machine, preserves the invariant that authored declarations select the state-machine name, allows validation and execution to share a pure resolver, and gives deterministic file roots for rhei-local, Panta-inherited, and built-in fallback cases.
