runtime/logs/task-point-state-machine-resolution-discuss-point-codex-yolo-openai-gpt-5.5.log:1510:./runtime/logs/task-point-state-machine-resolution-propose-solutions-codex-yolo-openai-gpt-5.5.log:257:./runtime/logs/task-point-inbox-hierarchy-propose-solutions-codex-yolo-openai-gpt-5.5.log:329:/home/vjovanov/f/rhei/skills/rhei-plan-writer/SKILL.md:54:Run `rhei states` in the project to discover the allowed state values, their agent instructions, and the declared transitions for the state machine the plan will follow. Use `rhei states --state-machine <path>` to target a specific YAML file (e.g. the one a plan's `**States:**` line references), and `--json` when machine-readable output is preferred. Use only state values reported by that command, follow the printed instructions when describing task work, and respect the declared transitions when choosing initial states.
